    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="487" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Clay</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 147.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 2, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 2d ultimo, No. 73,
                            informing this department of the confirmation, by the Emperor, of the
                            convention between Messrs. Sibley and Collins and the Russian
                            government, and of the orders subsequently given for the admission of
                            the men and material of the company into the Russian possessions, has
                            been received.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cassius M. Clay,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
